          {
            "text": "Despite being a [Multiple Head\nCase](https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MultipleHeadCase) Head\nCase, Kali view itself as a single being. While each head may think for\nitself, they are rarely in disagreement. one poison per head, harmless on\nits own, petrifies flesh if you get both [Snakes Are\nSinister](https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SnakesAreSinister)\nhttps://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SssssnakeTalk Kali is named\nafter both the Hindu goddess Kali, associated with time and death, and\nSaint Sara-la-Kâli, the Romani patron saint.",
